description: Number of nonisomorphic self-complementary circulant digraphs (Cayley digraphs for the cyclic group) of order 2n-1.
comments: There is an easy formula for prime orders. Formulae are also known for squarefree and prime-squared orders. The subsequent values for orders 29,31 are 596,1096.
links: V. A. Liskovets, Some identities for enumerators of circulant graphs.
V. A. Liskovets and R. Poeschel, On the enumeration of circulant graphs of prime-power and squarefree orders
author: _Valery A. Liskovets_
extensions: Further values for (twice) squarefree and (twice) prime-squared orders can be found in the Liskovets reference.
